      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "RUPEE'S ROCKET (4) was below best last time at this track (30.99) in a Grade 4/5, finishing a 5.5 lengths fourth. Has already won two times from this draw. Appeals as a leading chance in this. SOUTHPAW MCGRAW (1) settled back off the inside but went through his gears strongly to find the frame with a 3.5 lengths second (30.78) at this track in Grade 5. Didn't win last time but still ran one of the quickest times on the card. Will give a great sight again. FOXTON LOCH (8) has been beaten for early speed lately, last time finishing fourth (26.03) in a Grade 6 at this track. Solid beginner and with a good start should have clear running out wide. Better than last start and can bounce back. MONDO CORTEZ (2) cannot be written off despite a miss here at his latest outing.",
